5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REQUIRING A DISTRICT THAT USES TAX INCREMENT
6 FINANCING TO CREATE AN ADVISORY COMMITTEE; AND AMENDING SECTION SECTIONS 7-15-4234
7 AND 7-15-4282, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 7-15-4234, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "7-15-4234. Urban renewal agency to be administered by appointed board of commissioners --
13 advisory committee. (1) If the urban renewal agency is authorized to transact business and exercise powers
14 under this part, the mayor, by and with the advice and consent of the local governing body, shall appoint a
15 board of commissioners of the urban renewal agency consisting of five commissioners as provided in
16 subsection (2)(a) and an advisory committee as provided in subsection (2)(b).
17 (2) (a) The initial membership shall must consist of one commissioner appointed for 1 year, one for
18 2 years, one for 3 years, and two for 4 years. Each subsequent appointment must be for 4 years. A certificate of
19 the appointment or reappointment of a commissioner must be filed with the clerk of the municipality, and the
20 certificate is conclusive evidence of the proper appointment of the commissioner.
21 (b) The advisory committee shall provide advice to the urban renewal agency regarding the
22 administration of the urban renewal area. The committee must include at least one representative from the
23 county and one representative from a school district with boundaries that overlap with the urban renewal area.
24 The committee may include representatives of other taxing bodies with boundaries that overlap with the urban
25 renewal area.
26 (3) Each commissioner shall hold office until a successor has been appointed and has qualified.
27 (4) A commissioner may not receive compensation for services but is entitled to the necessary
28 expenses, including traveling expenses, incurred in the discharge of duties.
